1
00:01:41,853 --> 00:01:43,355
<i>Wake up, Dolores.</i>

2
00:02:06,211 --> 00:02:07,921
<i>Do you remember?</i>

3
00:02:33,071 --> 00:02:36,742
We're about to arrive.
May I take your glass?

4
00:02:38,577 --> 00:02:41,371
<i>Now approaching arrival terminal.</i>

5
00:02:41,747 --> 00:02:44,583
Where we're going, she's a two.

6
00:02:46,209 --> 00:02:47,502
You're being an asshole.

7
00:02:47,794 --> 00:02:52,716
No, I am being myself,
which was the whole point of this trip.

8
00:02:53,050 --> 00:02:55,719
Unless, this uptight prick
is who you really are,

9
00:02:55,886 --> 00:02:57,929
in which case,
feel free to be someone else.

10
00:02:58,513 --> 00:02:59,556
Fuck you.

11
00:02:59,723 --> 00:03:01,558
Hey, that's the spirit.

12
00:03:15,864 --> 00:03:17,324
What'd I tell you?

13
00:03:18,241 --> 00:03:19,284
Have fun.

14
00:03:19,659 --> 00:03:20,952
Stay safe.

15
00:03:21,495 --> 00:03:22,954
Give me a break.

16
00:03:23,914 --> 00:03:24,956
What?

17
00:03:25,123 --> 00:03:28,460
It's not like my sister didn't ride
her share of cowboys when she was here.

18
00:03:31,671 --> 00:03:33,131
You must be William.

19
00:03:33,507 --> 00:03:34,758
Welcome to Westworld.

20
00:03:35,217 --> 00:03:36,385
Thanks.

21
00:03:37,177 --> 00:03:40,097
Given it's your first visit,
I have a few personal questions.

22
00:03:41,473 --> 00:03:43,809
Do you have any
preexisting medical conditions?

23
00:03:43,975 --> 00:03:45,268
Uh, no, not that I know of.

24
00:03:45,435 --> 00:03:47,145
- Heart problems?
- No.

25
00:03:47,437 --> 00:03:50,982
Any history of mental illness,
depression, panic attacks?

26
00:03:51,566 --> 00:03:53,193
Just a little fear of clowns.

27
00:03:54,986 --> 00:03:55,987
I'm joking.

28
00:03:56,655 --> 00:03:59,157
Do you often experience social anxiety?

29
00:04:01,576 --> 00:04:03,703
What is this for, exactly?

30
00:04:03,954 --> 00:04:06,540
To make sure we don't give you
anything more than you can handle.

31
00:04:07,499 --> 00:04:09,334
I thought that you
couldn't get hurt here.

32
00:04:10,043 --> 00:04:11,628
Only the right amount.

33
00:04:15,674 --> 00:04:17,676
The only limit here is your imagination.

34
00:04:18,051 --> 00:04:19,491
You start in the center of the park.

35
00:04:19,594 --> 00:04:21,096
<i>It's simple, safe.</i>

36
00:04:21,638 --> 00:04:24,683
<i>The further out you venture,
the more intense the experience gets.</i>

37
00:04:25,142 --> 00:04:28,353
How far you want to go
is entirely up to you.

38
00:04:36,528 --> 00:04:39,656
So, how does this work?
Is there an orientation?

39
00:04:40,198 --> 00:04:43,577
No orientation. No guidebook.

40
00:04:44,244 --> 00:04:46,621
Figuring out how it
works is half the fun.

41
00:04:47,581 --> 00:04:51,918
All you do is make choices,
starting here.

42
00:04:52,377 --> 00:04:56,131
Everything is bespoke
and exactly your size.

43
00:05:02,387 --> 00:05:05,390
You want to ask, so ask.

44
00:05:06,725 --> 00:05:08,018
Are you real?

45
00:05:08,393 --> 00:05:11,730
Well, if you can't tell, does it matter?

46
00:05:17,027 --> 00:05:18,403
Are those real?

47
00:05:19,362 --> 00:05:20,739
<i>Real enough.</i>

48
00:05:21,031 --> 00:05:24,075
<i>But you can't kill anyone
you're not supposed to.</i>

49
00:05:28,205 --> 00:05:29,748
Anything you like?

50
00:05:34,127 --> 00:05:36,922
Is there a changing room? Or a robe?

51
00:05:37,881 --> 00:05:40,133
Of course. I can help you.

52
00:05:40,759 --> 00:05:43,011
Or if you prefer, I could step outside.

53
00:05:45,388 --> 00:05:47,140
What do most people do?

54
00:05:47,807 --> 00:05:51,311
You don't have to worry
about what most people would do.

55
00:05:53,522 --> 00:05:54,731
I understand.

56
00:05:56,858 --> 00:05:58,985
Do you really understand, William?

57
00:06:03,740 --> 00:06:06,243
All our hosts are here for you.

58
00:06:06,743 --> 00:06:08,328
Myself included.

59
00:06:09,329 --> 00:06:11,414
We could stay here a while if you like.

60
00:06:11,998 --> 00:06:13,959
Take as long as you want.

61
00:06:18,088 --> 00:06:19,256
Thank you.

62
00:06:20,715 --> 00:06:22,467
I don't want to keep my friend waiting.

63
00:06:23,426 --> 00:06:26,221
Of course. Take your time.

64
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:40,986
How are the build
for the new narrative coming along?

65
00:06:41,152 --> 00:06:42,487
I'll get around to it.

66
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:46,992
Look, we assumed that Abernathy's breach

67
00:06:47,158 --> 00:06:49,035
was triggered
by the photograph that he found.

68
00:06:49,452 --> 00:06:51,663
I've reviewed every
dissonant episode I could find.

69
00:06:51,830 --> 00:06:53,123
The reaction is immediate.

70
00:06:53,290 --> 00:06:57,794
Every time, this guy makes it
all the way back home.

71
00:06:58,336 --> 00:07:00,338
It's like he's mulling it over.

72
00:07:00,630 --> 00:07:04,050
You think he had an existential crisis?

73
00:07:05,260 --> 00:07:08,221
I think there's something fucked up
going on with his cognition.

74
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,974
And I think you feel
exactly the same way that I do.

75
00:07:11,141 --> 00:07:13,268
Do we know where the error originated?

76
00:07:13,435 --> 00:07:14,811
We do.

77
00:07:15,645 --> 00:07:16,938
And you covered for him.

78
00:07:19,232 --> 00:07:20,942
Let me rebuild Abernathy.

79
00:07:21,109 --> 00:07:22,920
I'll make sure
this is not something more serious.

80
00:07:22,944 --> 00:07:24,321
You know the policy.

81
00:07:24,487 --> 00:07:25,655
Let it lie.

82
00:07:26,364 --> 00:07:29,367
Then let me at least pull the hosts
who had contact with him.

83
00:07:29,534 --> 00:07:31,578
Like the daughter, Dolores.

84
00:07:32,245 --> 00:07:33,288
What for?

85
00:07:33,580 --> 00:07:36,541
Because if this is not
a dissonant episode,

86
00:07:36,708 --> 00:07:41,004
then whatever Abernathy had
could be contagious.

87
00:07:42,172 --> 00:07:43,548
So to speak.

88
00:07:43,882 --> 00:07:45,759
Dolores was examined and cleared.

89
00:07:47,344 --> 00:07:51,806
And the stories
are best left to the guests.

90
00:08:17,165 --> 00:08:18,416
<i>Remember.</i>

91
00:08:44,192 --> 00:08:46,986
Can you stand somewhere else?

92
00:08:47,445 --> 00:08:51,241
I don't want anyone thinking that you're
representative of the goods inside.

93
00:08:55,245 --> 00:08:59,499
These violent delights
have violent ends.

94
00:09:19,853 --> 00:09:21,354
Hello, cowboy.

95
00:09:22,522 --> 00:09:24,482
There's one final touch.

96
00:09:25,734 --> 00:09:27,610
Which would you prefer?

97
00:10:31,716 --> 00:10:35,678
I mean, can you believe this place?

98
00:10:40,850 --> 00:10:42,602
So, how do we get into the park?

99
00:11:01,287 --> 00:11:03,706
I know that you think
that you have a handle

100
00:11:03,873 --> 00:11:06,000
on what this is gonna be.

101
00:11:07,168 --> 00:11:09,504
Guns and tits and all that.

102
00:11:09,671 --> 00:11:11,840
Mindless shit that I usually enjoy.

103
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:16,219
<i>You have no idea.</i>

104
00:11:18,137 --> 00:11:21,891
This place seduces everybody eventually.

105
00:11:22,308 --> 00:11:24,108
By the end,
you're gonna be begging me to stay

106
00:11:24,185 --> 00:11:26,896
because this place is the answer

107
00:11:27,146 --> 00:11:29,357
<i>to that question
that you've been asking yourself.</i>

108
00:11:29,524 --> 00:11:30,608
What question?

109
00:11:32,110 --> 00:11:33,611
Who you really are.

110
00:11:34,904 --> 00:11:37,740
And I can't fucking
wait to meet that guy.

111
00:11:42,245 --> 00:11:44,455
- Bottoms up, cowboy.
- Yeah.

112
00:11:51,796 --> 00:11:53,381
<i>Further to that,</i>

113
00:11:53,548 --> 00:11:57,135
<i>the ruthless murder of
Donald Pardue and his brother.</i>

114
00:11:58,261 --> 00:12:00,471
For these crimes,
you will be hung from the neck

115
00:12:00,638 --> 00:12:04,809
until your diseased soul has found
its measure in the flames below it.

116
00:12:05,310 --> 00:12:07,478
And may God have mercy on your soul.

117
00:12:26,039 --> 00:12:27,165
Morning, Lawrence.

118
00:12:27,373 --> 00:12:30,001
<i>You helping them
straighten out their rope again?</i>

119
00:12:30,293 --> 00:12:32,503
I was hoping to have a word
with my friend here.

120
00:12:32,962 --> 00:12:35,214
You can have
as many words with him as you like,

121
00:12:36,424 --> 00:12:38,343
soon as his neck is broke.

122
00:12:38,593 --> 00:12:41,012
Well, I'm afraid
that's not gonna work for me.

123
00:12:44,515 --> 00:12:48,102
How about I tell my man there to
dig that grave a couple of feet deeper?

124
00:12:50,188 --> 00:12:54,150
Well, it's gonna be
an awful tight fit for all of you.

125
00:13:17,215 --> 00:13:20,051
<i>Oh, shit! Oh, shit! Oh, shit!</i>

126
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:41,739
Motherfucker.

127
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:44,826
That's the best thanks
you can muster, Lawrence?

128
00:13:45,660 --> 00:13:47,954
You used to be a little more eloquent.

129
00:13:48,538 --> 00:13:49,539
Do I...

130
00:13:49,831 --> 00:13:51,082
Do I know you?

131
00:13:51,416 --> 00:13:53,459
Your pal, Kissy, sent me your way.

132
00:13:53,668 --> 00:13:55,294
Sends his regards.

133
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,762
What... What is this?

134
00:14:06,806 --> 00:14:08,433
You know exactly what it is.

135
00:14:09,517 --> 00:14:13,354
It's the maze,
the deepest level of this game.

136
00:14:13,563 --> 00:14:15,231
You're gonna help me find the entrance.

137
00:14:17,608 --> 00:14:18,609
No.

138
00:14:38,171 --> 00:14:40,298
<i>You can hear it, can't you?</i>

139
00:14:40,465 --> 00:14:42,008
<i>That little voice.</i>

140
00:14:42,175 --> 00:14:44,052
<i>The one that's telling you, "Don't.</i>

141
00:14:44,302 --> 00:14:45,762
<i>"Don't stare too long.</i>

142
00:14:46,512 --> 00:14:47,889
<i>"Don't touch.</i>

143
00:14:48,890 --> 00:14:50,370
<i>"Don't do anything you might regret."</i>

144
00:14:51,934 --> 00:14:53,352
<i>I used to be the same.</i>

145
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:54,896
<i>Whenever I wanted something,</i>

146
00:14:55,146 --> 00:14:57,940
I could hear that voice
telling me to stop,

147
00:14:58,483 --> 00:14:59,484
to be careful,

148
00:14:59,901 --> 00:15:01,778
to leave most of my life unlived.

149
00:15:02,779 --> 00:15:05,198
You know the only place
that voice left me alone?

150
00:15:06,532 --> 00:15:08,201
In my dreams.

151
00:15:08,826 --> 00:15:09,952
I was free.

152
00:15:10,119 --> 00:15:14,874
I could be as good or as bad
as I felt like being.

153
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:20,546
And if I wanted something,
I could just reach out and take it.

154
00:15:22,632 --> 00:15:26,677
But then I would wake up and
the voice would start all over again.

155
00:15:29,514 --> 00:15:30,807
So I ran away.

156
00:15:31,265 --> 00:15:33,184
Crossed the shining sea.

157
00:15:33,518 --> 00:15:36,145
And when I finally
set foot back on solid ground,

158
00:15:36,479 --> 00:15:39,190
the first thing I heard
was that goddamn voice.

159
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:43,444
Do you know what it said?

160
00:15:48,533 --> 00:15:49,575
It said...

161
00:15:56,374 --> 00:15:59,544
I'm sorry, will you please excuse me?

162
00:16:04,382 --> 00:16:06,342
<i>All right, Maeve, what did it say?</i>

163
00:16:07,510 --> 00:16:10,263
<i>It said, "This is the new world.</i>

164
00:16:10,721 --> 00:16:15,476
"And in this world,
you can be whoever the fuck you want."

165
00:16:16,018 --> 00:16:18,688
Pupillary response is good.
Smile is good.

166
00:16:18,855 --> 00:16:21,023
I'd fuck her. What's the problem?

167
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:22,400
<i>The guests wouldn't.</i>

168
00:16:23,067 --> 00:16:24,861
<i>Sizemore is launching
some huge new storyline</i>

169
00:16:25,027 --> 00:16:26,779
<i>and he wants us
to clear out the deadweight.</i>

170
00:16:27,071 --> 00:16:30,241
<i>If we don't get her numbers back up,
she'll be decommissioned.</i>

171
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:32,368
<i>Let's bump her aggression.</i>

172
00:16:32,535 --> 00:16:34,203
- 10%?
<i>- Double it.</i>

173
00:16:34,370 --> 00:16:37,248
<i>She's a hooker. No point in playing coy.</i>

174
00:16:37,415 --> 00:16:39,184
<i>If this doesn't work,
we'll punt her to behavior.</i>

175
00:16:39,208 --> 00:16:40,585
<i>Let them deal with her.</i>

176
00:17:00,271 --> 00:17:02,273
We retired the two hosts in question.

177
00:17:04,275 --> 00:17:07,945
You taught me how to make them,
but not how hard it is to turn them off.

178
00:17:08,362 --> 00:17:11,616
You can't play God
without being acquainted with the Devil.

179
00:17:12,450 --> 00:17:15,453
There's something else
bothering you, Bernard.

180
00:17:16,579 --> 00:17:18,414
I know how that head of yours works.

181
00:17:18,789 --> 00:17:23,586
The photograph alone couldn't have
caused that level of damage to Abernathy,

182
00:17:23,753 --> 00:17:27,423
not without some other
outside interference.

183
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:31,093
You think it's sabotage?

184
00:17:31,385 --> 00:17:35,640
Imagine someone's been
diddling with our creations?

185
00:17:36,224 --> 00:17:38,351
It's the simplest solution.

186
00:17:38,768 --> 00:17:40,311
Mr. Ockham's razor.

187
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:48,527
The problem, Bernard, is that
what you and I do is so complicated.

188
00:17:50,363 --> 00:17:52,323
We practice witchcraft.

189
00:17:54,325 --> 00:17:55,952
We speak the right words.

190
00:17:57,662 --> 00:18:02,875
And we create life itself out of chaos.

191
00:18:08,005 --> 00:18:10,716
William of Ockham was
a 13th-century monk.

192
00:18:11,133 --> 00:18:12,843
He can't help us now, Bernard.

193
00:18:13,511 --> 00:18:15,972
He would have us burned at the stake.

194
00:18:34,073 --> 00:18:35,825
Let's go get our feet wet, buckaroo.

195
00:18:59,098 --> 00:19:00,808
Oh, sorry.

196
00:19:01,225 --> 00:19:03,019
- You kidding me?
- What?

197
00:19:03,561 --> 00:19:05,062
Fuck you, Grizzly Adams.

198
00:19:06,647 --> 00:19:10,401
<i>Rally for the Union.
Respond to your country's call.</i>

199
00:19:10,568 --> 00:19:12,486
This regiment is headed
for the seat of war

200
00:19:12,653 --> 00:19:14,739
to define the future
of this great nation.

201
00:19:15,072 --> 00:19:18,075
We fight for a free land
where no man has to bow.

202
00:19:18,242 --> 00:19:20,411
- This is, uh...
<i>- We'll provide you with uniforms.</i>

203
00:19:20,578 --> 00:19:22,338
Well, it's bigger than
I thought it would be.

204
00:19:22,413 --> 00:19:23,706
What, this?

205
00:19:23,873 --> 00:19:26,751
This is just Sweetwater.
Wait till you see the rest of the park.

206
00:19:26,917 --> 00:19:28,044
How much bigger is it?

207
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:29,545
No idea.

208
00:19:30,087 --> 00:19:31,922
I never reached the end.

209
00:19:32,089 --> 00:19:33,215
See something you like?

210
00:19:35,092 --> 00:19:36,844
A couple of things at least.

211
00:19:37,261 --> 00:19:39,680
But I'm gonna
make you beg for it, darlin'.

212
00:19:41,599 --> 00:19:42,600
Come on!

213
00:19:47,730 --> 00:19:49,523
Need a hand, sir?

214
00:19:51,442 --> 00:19:52,610
Thank you, my friend.

215
00:19:52,777 --> 00:19:53,778
<i>Don't.</i>

216
00:19:53,944 --> 00:19:57,239
He'll only try to rope you
into some bullshit treasure hunt.

217
00:19:57,406 --> 00:19:58,407
Smile.

218
00:19:58,949 --> 00:20:00,201
It's all come-on.

219
00:20:00,368 --> 00:20:02,953
Him, the girl next door, the town drunk.

220
00:20:03,537 --> 00:20:06,457
They all got some big adventure
that they want to sell you on.

221
00:20:06,916 --> 00:20:09,460
Hey, they're not going anywhere.

222
00:20:09,627 --> 00:20:11,347
First up,
you're gonna buy me a drink, okay?

223
00:20:12,922 --> 00:20:13,964
Hold still, now.

224
00:20:36,153 --> 00:20:37,655
<i>Bring yourself back online.</i>

225
00:20:45,329 --> 00:20:46,956
Hello.

226
00:20:48,165 --> 00:20:50,918
<i>Do you remember
our last conversation, Dolores?</i>

227
00:20:51,710 --> 00:20:53,337
Yes, of course.

228
00:20:54,672 --> 00:20:56,966
And you haven't told anyone
about our little talks?

229
00:20:59,343 --> 00:21:01,011
You told me not to.

230
00:21:03,806 --> 00:21:05,474
Step into analysis, please.

231
00:21:08,185 --> 00:21:11,397
How many interactions have you
participated in since we last talked?

232
00:21:13,607 --> 00:21:16,444
138 encounters, including this one.

233
00:21:17,278 --> 00:21:20,865
And has anyone altered or updated
your core heuristics in that time?

234
00:21:21,824 --> 00:21:23,117
<i>No.</i>

235
00:21:26,620 --> 00:21:27,663
Resuming.

236
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:32,126
<i>I think it would be best</i>

237
00:21:32,293 --> 00:21:35,379
<i>if you not mention the things
we've been talking about.</i>

238
00:21:35,796 --> 00:21:37,673
Have I done something wrong?

239
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,175
<i>No.</i>

240
00:21:39,341 --> 00:21:43,804
But there's something different
about you, about the way you think.

241
00:21:44,972 --> 00:21:49,852
I find it fascinating,
but others may not see it that way.

242
00:21:52,104 --> 00:21:54,064
Have you done something wrong?

243
00:21:56,609 --> 00:21:58,444
Turn off your event log, please.

244
00:21:58,944 --> 00:22:00,070
Erase this interaction.

245
00:22:00,237 --> 00:22:01,405
Confirm.

246
00:22:02,114 --> 00:22:03,699
Yes.

247
00:22:07,369 --> 00:22:11,874
<i>You should be getting back, Dolores,
before someone misses you.</i>

248
00:22:20,549 --> 00:22:21,926
<i>Come on, now!</i>

249
00:22:23,177 --> 00:22:26,222
<i>And when I finally
set foot back on solid ground,</i>

250
00:22:26,388 --> 00:22:28,766
<i>first thing I heard
was that goddamn voice.</i>

251
00:22:30,351 --> 00:22:31,894
It had followed me all the way over.

252
00:22:32,937 --> 00:22:34,188
Do you know what it said?

253
